    &lt;CommentText&gt;Following GP referral was seen within  8 days..Seen  by a  Doctor,  Mammogram, Ultrasound, biopsy followed up by Doctor to sum up the morning. Spent about 4 hours there. The staff were all kind and worked in harmony.  It was a busy clinic.From the reviews I have read it appears people are given biopsy results within or about one week following their visit.  I was told that I would be seen 2 weeks later.  Computers were not working,  appointment list was full for the date that I was advised to write in my diary. Tuesday 13th August 2019.  I woiuld be added to end of this list.  Today  I have received an appointment for the out patients department Bay 4..  To see the same consultant! This is a different place to the Elm Unit. My concern is knowing just how bad the Appointment system is at KGH and Queens Hospital. When told by powers that be, you will be seen by a consultant and it doesn't happen.  To be asked by someone why are you here or what have you come for? We have personal experience wth my husband  how bad it can be it is .a constant battle. The Elm Unit at KGH clearly isn't coping with the number of people they see&lt;/CommentText&gt;
